<subSubSection id="230509EC115A62142383CD95DA25B2E1" pageId="8" pageNumber="87" type="derivation of specific epithet">
<paragraph id="C931A2966FAADE834181C1F1FA352C39" pageId="8" pageNumber="87">Derivation of specific epithet.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F205FF6C0AB5304CE738E8CB02758BC7" pageId="8" pageNumber="87">
The epithet 
<normalizedToken id="B852AD384BF5B440FEDBD0278E1BD756" originalValue="“belvedere”">
&quot; 
<emphasis id="2C58CD3C4AEAA92B049A09EE4044D1A2" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="87">belvedere</emphasis>
&quot;
</normalizedToken>
is a singular Latinized masculine noun in apposition, based on the name of the area in which these beetles are found.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
